dt-option.default:
        The default value for the `-init searchPanes.cascadePanes` paramater is `false`. When this default value is in place no action will be taken to cascade the panes.


        As standard, SearchPanes will display all of the options for that column throughout its operation. When `-init searchPanes.cascadePanes` is set to `true`, the panes will remove options which are no longer present in the currently displayed DataTable. The cascade action will occur when a selection or a deselection is made in one of the panes.

		This is useful when dealing with large data sets with many different options as they are narrowed down accordingly as operation proceeds.





$(document).ready(function() {
    $('#example').DataTable( {
        searchPanes:{
            cascadePanes: true
        }
    });
});
